Runtime¶

In [ ]:
# Calculate the IQR for runtime
Q1 = movie_titles['runtime'].quantile(0.25)
Q3 = movie_titles['runtime'].quantile(0.75)
IQR = Q3 - Q1

# Filter out the outliers using the IQR method
titles_no_outliers = movie_titles[(movie_titles['runtime'] >= Q1 - 1.5 * IQR) & (movie_titles['runtime'] <= Q3 + 1.5 * IQR)]

# Prepare the independent and dependent variables for regression analysis
X = titles_no_outliers['release_year'].values.reshape(-1, 1)
y = titles_no_outliers['runtime'].values

# Transform the independent variable to create polynomial features
poly = PolynomialFeatures(degree=2)
X_poly = poly.fit_transform(X)

# Perform the polynomial regression analysis
poly_reg = LinearRegression()
poly_reg.fit(X_poly, y)

# Create a scatter plot of the data points
plt.scatter(X, y, color='yellow', alpha=0.5, label='Data Points')

# Calculate the polynomial regression line points
X_line = np.linspace(X.min(), X.max(), num=1000).reshape(-1, 1)
X_line_poly = poly.transform(X_line)
y_line = poly_reg.predict(X_line_poly)

# Plot the polynomial regression line
plt.plot(X_line, y_line, color='red', linewidth=2, label='Polynomial Regression Line')

# Add labels, title, and legend to the plot
plt.xlabel('Release Year')
plt.ylabel('Runtime')
plt.title('Quadratic Polynomial Regression: Release Year vs Runtime (1920-2020) without Outliers')
plt.legend()

# Display the plot
plt.show()

# Filter the titles DataFrame to include only movies released between 1920 and 1960
filtered_titles_yr20to60 = movie_titles[(movie_titles['release_year'] >= 1920) & (movie_titles['release_year'] <= 1960)]

# Calculate the IQR for runtime
Q1 = filtered_titles_yr20to60['runtime'].quantile(0.25)
Q3 = filtered_titles_yr20to60['runtime'].quantile(0.75)
IQR = Q3 - Q1

# Filter out the outliers using the IQR method
filtered_titles_yr20to60_no_outliers = filtered_titles_yr20to60[(filtered_titles_yr20to60['runtime'] >= Q1 - 1.5 * IQR) & (filtered_titles_yr20to60['runtime'] <= Q3 + 1.5 * IQR)]

# Prepare the independent and dependent variables for regression analysis
X = filtered_titles_yr20to60_no_outliers['release_year']
X = sm.add_constant(X)  # Add a constant term to the independent variables
y = filtered_titles_yr20to60_no_outliers['runtime']

# Perform the regression analysis
ols = sm.OLS(y, X).fit()

# Create a scatter plot of the data points
plt.scatter(X['release_year'], y, color='green', alpha=0.5, label='Data Points')

# Calculate the regression line points using the estimated coefficients
regression_line = ols.params[0] + ols.params[1] * np.array(X['release_year'])

# Plot the regression line
plt.plot(X['release_year'], regression_line, color='orange', linewidth=2, label='Regression Line')

# Add labels, title, and legend to the plot
plt.xlabel('Release Year')
plt.ylabel('Runtime')
plt.title('Correlation between Release Year and Runtime (1920-1960) without Outliers')
plt.legend()

# Display the plot
plt.show()

Model Selection¶

In [ ]:
# compare lr, random forest, and svr

r2 = []
mse = []
labels = ['Linear Regression', 'Random Forest', 'Support Vector Regression']
pred_lr, pred_rf, pred_svr  = lr_best.predict(X_test),  rf_best.predict(X_test),  svr_best.predict(X_test)

predictions = [pred_lr, pred_rf, pred_svr ]
for i in range(3):
    mse_i = mean_squared_error(y_test, predictions[i])
    mse.append(mse_i)
    if i == 0:
        r2.append(lr_best.rsquared)
    else:
        r2_i = r2_score(y_test,  predictions[i])
        r2.append(r2_i)
    
results = {'Model': labels, 'R Squared': r2, 'Mean Square Error': mse}
results = pd.DataFrame(results)
results['R Squared'] = results['R Squared'].round(2)
results = results.sort_values(by='Mean Square Error')

for i, bar in enumerate(plot_r2.ax.containers):
    plot_r2.ax.bar_label(bar, label_type='edge', fontsize=10, padding=2)
plt.title('Model Performance Comparison (R^2)')

plt.show()
